Turkey Equity Movers: Arcelik, Garanti, Saglam GYO, Sinpas GYO

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-07-06T15:41:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/turkey-equity-movers-anel-elektrik-albaraka-turk-arcelik-koc.html
Turkey ’s benchmark ISE National 100
Index fell 626.15, or 1 percent, to 63,240.11 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in Istanbul, a second day of declines.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Arcelik AS (ARCLK)  , Turkey’s biggest and  Europe ’s third-
largest home appliance maker, slumped 22 kurus, or 2.7 percent,
to 8.08 liras. The company is contacting customers in the  United
Kingdom  to perform on-site fixes to its Beko branded
refrigerators that London fire officials say may pose a fire
hazard, it said in an e-mail late yesterday.  Saglam Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (SAGYO)  , a
Turkish real estate investment trust owned by food group Yildiz
Holding AS, rose for a fifth day to the highest since 2007 on a
plan to merge with real estate developer Saf Gayrimenkul
Gelistirme Insaat & Ticaret AS. Saglam GYO gained 19 kurus, or
16 percent, to 1.40 liras. The shares have jumped 52 percent
since their July 1 close.  Sinpas Gayrimenkul Yatirim Ortakligi AS (SNGYO)  , a part-
owner of Saf, added 8 kurus, or 4.2 percent, to 1.99 liras, its
highest since May 20.  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  , Turkey’s largest
lender by market volume, fell 18 kurus, or 2.4 percent, to 7.32
liras. Turkish banking industry profits fell 18.4 percent in May
compared with the previous year, the regulator in Ankara
reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
